MODULE 3: CD INTEGRATION (CONTINUOUS DELIVERY / CONTINUOUS DEPLOYMENT)
====================================================================

1. Introduction
CD Integration refers to integrating Continuous Delivery and Continuous Deployment practices into the software development lifecycle. It enables frequent, reliable, and automated software releases.

2. What is Continuous Delivery?
Continuous Delivery ensures software is always in a deployable state through automated build, test, and release processes.

3. What is Continuous Deployment?
Continuous Deployment automatically releases validated changes to production without manual approval.

4. Difference Between Continuous Delivery and Continuous Deployment
Continuous Delivery:
- Deployment is ready.
- Human approval required.

Continuous Deployment:
- Deployment is automatic.
- No manual approval required.

5. CD Pipeline Stages
Code Commit
      ↓
Build
      ↓
Automated Testing
      ↓
Quality Checks
      ↓
Deployment
      ↓
Monitoring

6. Key Components
A. Source Control
Examples:
- Git
- GitHub
- Azure Repos

B. Build Automation
Examples:
- Maven
- Gradle
- MSBuild

C. Testing Automation
- Unit testing
- Integration testing
- Regression testing

D. Deployment Automation
- Scripts
- Containers
- Kubernetes

7. Benefits of CD Integration
- Faster releases.
- Reduced risk.
- Improved quality.
- More reliable deployments.
- Faster feedback.

8. CI/CD Relationship
Continuous Integration (CI)
Developers frequently merge code.

Continuous Delivery (CD)
Software remains deployable.

Continuous Deployment
Automatic production release.

9. DevOps and CD
CD is a major practice within DevOps. It supports collaboration between development and operations teams through automation and monitoring.

10. Common CD Tools
- Azure DevOps
- Jenkins
- GitHub Actions
- GitLab CI/CD
- Bamboo
- Argo CD

11. Deployment Strategies
A. Blue-Green Deployment
Two production environments exist.
One receives the new version.

B. Canary Deployment
Release to a small group of users.

C. Rolling Deployment
Gradually replace existing instances.

12. Monitoring After Deployment
- Application performance.
- Error rates.
- User experience metrics.
- Infrastructure health.

13. Security in CD Pipelines
- Access control.
- Secret management.
- Vulnerability scanning.
- Dependency checks.
- Compliance verification.

14. Challenges
- Complex environments.
- Pipeline maintenance.
- Security concerns.
- Tool integration.
- Legacy systems.

15. Best Practices
- Automate testing.
- Maintain version control.
- Deploy frequently.
- Monitor continuously.
- Secure pipeline credentials.
- Use infrastructure as code.

16. Real-World Example
A software team pushes code to GitHub. CI builds and tests the application. CD deploys the application to staging automatically. After validation, production deployment is performed quickly and reliably.

17. Interview Questions
- What is Continuous Delivery?
- What is Continuous Deployment?
- Difference between CI and CD?
- Name common CI/CD tools.
- Explain Blue-Green deployment.
- Explain Canary deployment.



